defaultBritain
default’s interest in 
defaultIndia
default; 
defaultBritish India
default was really Persian-speaking before it was English-speaking. There were cultural inroads into that sort of Persian mindset and Iranian outlook and attitudes; that has, for obvious reasons, been dissipated in the past 50 or so years. There is still a good and growing set of expertise. As someone who promotes Iranian and 
defaultPersianate
default studies around the 
defaultUK
